      conclusion: "The return of Christ is not a theological oddity to be managed or defended. It is the future that gives the present its weight. Jim Elliot was not a fool for giving what he could not keep. He was the wisest man in the room — the one who had done the eternal calculation correctly. And his life, not only his death, was the proof.",
